This paper is primarily focused on facial landmark detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the prediction of attributes such as gender and age, which are common applications of machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG). The authors also mention the use of benchmarks to validate their approach, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of their approach on computation, which is relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
